# DevQuest Rules

Read `vision.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, and `README.md` before generating code.

- Keep code simple. Avoid overengineering.
- Prefer functions over classes.
- No service layer unless necessary.
- Keep files under 250 lines.
- Use Rich for terminal UI.
- Use SQLite for persistence.
- Preserve CLI UX — every command should feel like a game.
- Never break existing commands (`hero init`, `status`, `commit`, `push`).
- XP and Gold only after real developer actions succeed.
- Always favor readability.
